    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. The 6 not-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 1. Validation results demonstrate that the CFD model predicts pump pressure rise within 4.2% of experimental measurements and that the relative hemolysis index satisfies RH < 1 across all 5 operating conditions. The grid independence study confirms numerical accuracy of the discretization scheme. The model is judged credible for the intended use of identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
